
---

## Markdown basics

| You type | It shows as |
|----------|-------------|
| `# Title` | Large heading |
| `## Section` | Smaller heading |
| `- item` | Bullet list |
| `` `code` `` | Inline code |
| `[text](url)` | Link |

---

## Tips

1. **Exact name:** `README.md` (capital README, `.md` extension).
2. **Location:** project root (same level as `.gitignore`, `LICENSE`).
3. **First commit:** include README with license and `.gitignore` if the assignment wants one scaffold commit.

---

## After you create it

1. Push to GitHub (if local).
2. Refresh **https://github.com/Oriba-Sahar05/capstone-project** — README should appear on the main page.
3. Ask Cursor to critique it and apply one improvement (part of your assignment).

If you want, I can give you a **full README** tailored to your capstone app idea — say what you’re building (e.g. todo app, blog, API).
